-- Club Med Offers EU80 Million of Convertible Bonds to Extend Debt Maturity
-- B y   D a v i d   W h i t e h o u s e
-- 2010-09-29T06:32:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-29/club-med-offers-eu80-million-of-convertible-bonds-to-extend-debt-maturity.html
Club Mediterranee SA said it will
seek to sell 80 million euros of convertible bonds expiring in
November 2015 to lengthen its debt-maturity profile.  The company will offer to buy back existing convertible bonds
expiring in November, it said in an emailed statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Whitehouse at 
 dwhitehouse1@bloomberg.net  